<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910416-0083</DOCNO><DOCID>910416-0083.</DOCID><HL>   REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:   Kitty Sick</HL><DATE>04/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A20</SO><LP>   Gary Sick is the Kitty Kelley of foreign affairs. Mr.Sick, a former Carter national-security official, haspublished a long account of a purported deal between Reagancampaign officials and various Iranians in 1980 to delay therelease of the American hostages until after the election.The account has various sources alleging that avice-presidential candidate, George Bush, managed todisappear from the campaign for three days in October to do adeal with the Iranians in Paris. But in the new Kelleyesqueapproach to history, only one named source &quot;out of hundredsof interviews&quot; appears. Even the mournful hostage who endsthe piece -- &quot;It's too painful to think about&quot; -- has noname. Sources Anonymous.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>